cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with neural translation of speech. It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with speech transcription. Additionally, it involves the use of regularization techniques, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the use of multitask learning and attention mechanisms could also place it in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
